HEADWORD: Halfer
<hw>Half"er</hw> <pr>(-⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who possesses or gives half only; one who shares.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp. Montagu.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A male fallow deer gelded.</def> <rj><au>Pegge
(1814).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Half-faced</ent>⟦br⟧
